<br>
Terrorism doesn't work, as Ghie noted above.  It doesn't persuade.  It doesn't enlist.  What it generally does is get people very pissed off at the perpetrators.  Now what does this resemble?<br>
<br>
Trolls never persuade people with their outlandish arguements.  It doesn't garner people to their side.  The most extreme cases are usually from anonymous or one-shot sources (like terrorists hiding in caves, avoiding claiming responsibility).  It does, however, garner the troller a LOT of attention.<br>
<br>
Maybe this is a paralel.  And no, the paralel is NOT NOT NOT that trolls and terrorists are the same type of person.  Please do NOT put that into my mouth.<br>
<br>
But maybe, just maybe, the impetus for the action is similar.  Maybe the feeling of being separated from main stream society, of feeling like no one notices you, of having this pain or desire that no one else seems to care about, cause anti-social and extreme action--and action guaranteed to get a reaction.<br>
<br>
Or maybe not.  I'm not a troller in general, and I'm definitely not a terrorist, so maybe the motivation is completely different.  It is a theory though. <p>Salenie Silkweaver<BR>Proud Member of <a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com">Clan Battle Axe</a> 



